org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.requirements

Interface DeriveReqt

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, Trace
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeriveReqtImpl

    public interface DeriveReqt
extends Trace
    A representation of the model object 'Derive Reqt'. A DeriveReqt relationship is a dependency between two requirements in which a client requirement can be derived from the supplier requirement. As with other dependencies, the arrow direction points from the derived (client) requirement to the (supplier) requirement from which it is derived.
    See Also:
    RequirementsPackage.getDeriveReqt()
